    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant paired with a tactile 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. This chassis exhibits excellent lateral rigidity and retains its factory-spec damping characteristics. Recent preventative maintenance includes an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal, ensuring the long-term integrity of the rotating assembly. The naturally aspirated induction system delivers linear torque across the rev range, while the hydraulic rack-and-pinion steering provides the communicative feedback synonymous with this era of Zuffenhausen engineering. While the Arctic Silver finish shows minor road patina consistent with spirited use, the mechanical synchronicity remains sharp, with crisp gear engagement and a robust, leak-free undercarriage.",
